# Agent & parallel job concurrency

This machine has limited RAM. **Never launch more concurrent Task subagents than logical CPU cores.**

## Subagent launches

1. Run `scripts/max_parallel_jobs.sh` (or `sysctl -n hw.logicalcpu` on macOS) to get the limit **N**.
2. Launch **at most N** Task subagents in parallel; wait for the batch to finish before starting the next.
3. Do **not** fan out dozens of agents in one turn (e.g. 20+ AHC solves at once).
4. Prefer batching related work into fewer agents when each task is small.

## Local parallelism (builds, testers, downloads)

- `make -j$(scripts/max_parallel_jobs.sh)`, `xargs -P $(scripts/max_parallel_jobs.sh)`, etc.
- Rust `cargo build` / AHC testers: avoid running many `cargo` builds simultaneously across contests.

## GPU

If GPU-backed agents exist, treat each GPU as one slot in the same cap (do not stack CPU + GPU agents beyond total core budget without user approval).
